| Feature | ConfigMap | Secret |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Purpose** | Non-sensitive settings (URLs, Names). | Sensitive data (Passwords, API Keys, Tokens). |
| **Security** | Plain text; easy to read. | Base64 encoded; slightly obscured. |
| **Usage** | Changing app behavior without code changes. | Protecting the infrastructure from unauthorized access. |
| **Memory** | Stored normally in the cluster. | Usually stored in `tmpfs` (RAM) on the node for better security. |

